Black First Land First (BLF) mourns the passing of one of its committed members, Comrade Busiswa Futshane, from Khayelitsha Cape Town. She was an active member who undertook all her tasks with the required seriousness and demanded the same kind of commitment to the revolution from the rest of the membership. BLF recognises her selflessness. Her dream was to see black people liberated through the return of our land. Comrade Busisiwe has passed on after a lengthy period of illness. BLF sends its sincere condolences to Comrade Busisiweâ€˜s family and friends. On our part, we commit to continue struggling until the ideals she so much cherished are realized. Issued by Black First Land First, National Coordinating Committee of (BLF NCC)
